> ```

The hypothesis `f_float ≥ 2^(−1021)` is **load-bearing, not parenthetical**. It is the proven domain of Conjecture C and the boundary of the proof's scaling-invariance mechanism.

### Five-line proof, no Sterbenz, fully deductive

> 1. By sign symmetry of IEEE 754 float negation: `round(x_term − 1) = −round(1 − x_term) = −f_float`.
> 2. Therefore `c2 = round(V_2 − f_float)`.
> 3. By Conjecture C (proven for `f_float ≥ 2^(−1021)`): `V_2 ≥ floor_binade(f_float)`, so `ulp(V_2) ≥ ulp(f_float)`.
