> 5. Small integer multiples of `ulp(f_float) = 2^(k−52)` are exactly representable in float64, so `round(V_2 − f_float) = V_2 − f_float = j · ulp(f_float)` exactly. **∎**

Load-bearing hypotheses: sign symmetry (IEEE 754), Conjecture C (proven, normal range), Part 2 error bound, scope gate (actual fixtures verified above floor).

